   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Solution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can begin by extracting just Miami-Dade county from the counties shapefile.\n",
    "As noted, the name is recorded in this file as just \"DADE\", so we can \n",
    "use that to get the correct county."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "md_county = fl_county.query(\"COUNTYNAME == 'DADE'\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The county shapefile uses a different crs, so we'll need to make them aligned before \n",
    "doing a join."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "md_county = md_county.to_crs({'init': 'epsg:2236', 'no_defs': True})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "md_polygon = md_county.iloc[0].geometry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we can select the MAZ centroids that are within the Miami-Dade polygon. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "md_maz = maz[maz.centroid.within(md_polygon)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then we merge `maz_data` dataframe with spatially joined `md_maz` \n",
    "to pull in the required population information. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can review a map of the selected MAZ's and the Miami-Dade County borders.\n",
    "Note that the MAZ's don't actually cover the whole county, as the south\n",
    "and west areas of the county are undeveloped swampland. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ax = md_maz_info.plot()\n",
    "md_county.plot(ax=ax, color='none', edgecolor='red');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Because the unit of measure in EPSG:2236 is approximately a foot, the\n",
    "`area` property of the `md_maz_info` GeoDataFrame gives the area in \n",
    "square feet.  To express population density in persons per square mile,\n",
    "we need to multiply by 5280 (feet per mile) squared."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "md_maz_info[\"Population Density\"] = md_maz_info.POP / md_maz_info.area * 5280**2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A first attempt at drawing a population density choropleth shows\n",
    "something is wrong; the entire county is displayed as nearly zero."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x648 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,9))\n",
    "ax.axis('off') # don't show axis\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Population Density\", fontweight='bold', fontsize=16)\n",
    "ax = md_maz_info.plot(ax=ax, column=\"Population Density\", legend=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The problem is identifiable in the legend: the scale goes up\n",
    "to nearly half a million people per square mile, which is \n",
    "an enormous value, and generally not achievable unless a zone\n",
    "is basically just skyscrapers.  This does apply to a handful of \n",
    "MAZ's in downtown Miami, but the density everywhere else is \n",
    "so much lower that this map is meaningless.\n",
    "\n",
    "We can create a more meaningful map by clipping the top of the\n",
    "range to a more reasonable value, say only 40,000 people per\n",
    "square mile."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x648 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,9))\n",
    "ax.axis('off') # don't show axis\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Population Density\", fontweight='bold', fontsize=16)\n",
    "ax = md_maz_info.plot(ax=ax, column=np.clip(md_maz_info[\"Population Density\"], 0, 40_000), legend=True)"
   ]
  }
